Green Public Procurement in The Netherlands
In 2005, the Dutch national government acknowledged a move in the House of Representatives to utilise
their annual spending power to promote the market for sustainable goods and services as well as to play
role model. Hence, a policy for environmentally friendly procurement was developed and
implemented across the national, local and provincial governments. Subsequently, sustainable public
procurement has expanded into a multidimensional policy in the Nether
based public procurement, international social criteria, social return
oriented public procurement and circular economy.
The Green Public Procurement (GPP) policy is
targeted at minimising the negative impacts of
production and consumption on the nature environment
. It includes a wide range of environmental criteria for different product groups that public
procure such as office equipment, uniforms, road works and catering. There
